57 attending the recounts.
58 (c) The custodian of voting machinestabulators shall
59 receive a salary in the amount of eight thousand nine hundred
60 dollars ($8,900)twenty-seven thousand dollars ($27,000) per
61 annum payable in equal monthly installments, effective upon
62 July 1, 2026. The Marshall County Commission, by resolution
63 adopted in a duly called meeting of the Marshall County
64 Commission, may provide for increases in the salary of the
65 custodian of voting tabulators beginning on June 1, 2028. The
66 salary shall be paid from the general fund of the county. and
67 before entering uponBefore beginning his or her duties, the
68 custodian shall be bonded in the sum of ten twenty thousand
69 dollars ($10,000)($20,000) for the faithful performance of his
70 or her duties as are other public officials."
71 Section 2. This act shall become effective on June 1,
72 2026.
